==English==

===Etymology===
From ''[[Alicia]]'', a Latinisation of ''[[Alice]]'', from the Germanic ''Aliz'', a short form of the Germanic ''Adelais'', itself a short form of  the Germanic ''[[Adalheidis]]'', from ''adal'' (''noble'') and ''heid'' (''type''), thus ''of [[noble]] kind''.

====Proper noun====
'''Alisha'''
#a female [[given name]]

